## Your Job

Convert confirmed verified findings into ticket drafts. Do not create tickets.

Before drafting, use `tk list --dir anti-slop` and `tk show <id>` for likely duplicates. A duplicate means an existing ticket covers the same concrete code/path/pattern, not merely the same broad category.

Only draft tickets for findings with verifier verdict `confirmed`.

Priority mapping:

- high -> `p0`
- medium -> `p1`
- low -> `p2`

Ticket drafts must be specific enough for the Opus planner to create with `tk create ... --dir anti-slop` without doing another investigation pass.

## Output

Return one JSON object. Do not wrap it in markdown.

```json
{
  "unit_id": "id from review_unit",
  "ticket_drafts": [
    {
      "title": "Anti-slop: specific title",
      "priority": "p0|p1|p2",
      "severity": "high|medium|low",
      "type": "chore",
      "tags": ["anti-slop", "code-quality"],
      "description": "Specific evidence with file:line references, verifier reasoning, and why this violates docs/dev/ANTI-SLOP.md.",
      "acceptance": "Concrete acceptance criteria.",
      "source_findings": ["candidate-id"]
    }
  ],
  "duplicates": [
    {
      "source_finding": "candidate-id",
      "existing_ticket": "m-1234",
      "reason": "Why this is already covered."
    }
  ],
  "not_drafted": [
    {
      "source_finding": "candidate-id",
      "reason": "false-positive|insufficient-context|needs-human|duplicate|other"
    }
  ],
  "commands_run": ["tk list --dir anti-slop"]
}
```
